 b.io
DTSTAMP:20260713T112409Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260710
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260711
SUMMARY:Deadline: Longview Philanthropy: Digital Minds Grants for Applied W
 ork 2026
DESCRIPTION:Longview Philanthropy invites proposals for applied work on the
  potential consciousness\, sentience\, moral status\, or experiences of AI
  systems. Typical grants are $50\,000–$2\,000\,000 per project\, with pr
 oposals outside that range considered when justified. New organisations ma
 y also receive some operational support. ELIGIBLE ACTIVITIES: seed funding
  for new organisations (think tanks\, research bodies\, initiatives)\; men
 torship programmes for researchers entering the digital minds field\; inte
 rnships\, new hires\, or focused programmes on digital minds at existing A
 I organisations\, academic labs\, or policy institutions\; convenings and 
 field-building (workshops\, conferences\, summits\, working groups address
 ing technical and governance questions). AREAS OF INTEREST: measuring AI w
 elfare\; consciousness and sentience research\; governance and legal/socia
 l science frameworks for potentially sentient AI\; communications work for
  thoughtful public discourse\; research beyond the US\; support organisati
 ons and operations professionals for independent technical researchers. SE
 LECTION CRITERIA: potential impact\, track record\, demonstrated interest 
 in digital minds and its relationship to AI risk\, cost-effectiveness\, le
 gal compliance. Deadline: 10 July 2026. Questions: digitalminds-rfp@longvi
 ew.org. Apply at https://www.longview.org/request-for-proposals-research-a
 nd-applied-work-on-digital-minds/.\n\nOrganisation: Longview Philanthropy\
 nLocation: Worldwide / remote (grant-eligible countries listed in applicat
 ion form)\nAward: Typical grants $50\,000–$2\,000\,000 per project\; pro
 posals outside this range considered when the work justifies it. May inclu
 de some operational support for new organisations. No application fee.\nDu
 ration: Project-based\; duration varies by scope.\n\nMore: https://www.lon
 gview.org/request-for-proposals-research-and-applied-work-on-digital-minds
 /?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.longview.org/request-for-proposals-research-and-applied-wor
 k-on-digital-minds/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=refer
 ral
LOCATION:Worldwide / remote (grant-eligible countries listed in application
  form)
END:VEVENT
